intents.label: adjust_plan
intents.description: Reorganize, restructure, rebalance, optimize, or revise entire schedule or plan. Broader than rescheduling single items.
examples: modify my schedule for exam week

intents.label: calendar_event
intents.description: Add a specific event with details (time, location, attendees) to the calendar. More structured than general scheduling.
examples: include the workshop in my events
add soccer practice tuesdays and thursdays
add graduation ceremony to my schedule

intents.label: cancel
intents.description: No, stop, abort, never mind, undo. Canceling or rejecting an action.

intents.label: chitchat
intents.description: Casual conversation, jokes, weather, small talk. Not task-related.

intents.label: confirm
intents.description: Yes, okay, sure, affirmative, I agree. Confirming an action.

intents.label: email
intents.description: Compose, draft, send, reply to, or forward an email message. Communication via email.
examples: compose email to hr about benefits
draft email to group about {task} milestone
send a message to my group members
hard_negatives: Creating tasks to send email (use task_management)

intents.label: greeting
intents.description: Hello, hi, hey, greetings. Starting a conversation.

intents.label: help
intents.description: Request assistance, tutorial, guide, instructions, or information about how to use features.

intents.label: reminder
intents.description: Set up a notification, alert, or reminder for a specific time or event. Prompt user to remember something.
examples: create a reminder for office hours
remind me to submit the form {date}
nudge me about car insurance renewal
notify me about the submission deadline
alert me when it's time for class
don't forget to lock door when leaving

intents.label: reschedule
intents.description: Move, postpone, delay, advance, shift, or change the time/date of an EXISTING event, meeting, or appointment.
examples: can we move the {event} to wednesday?
hard_negatives: Creating new events (use calendar_event or scheduling)

intents.label: scheduling
intents.description: Create, plan, arrange, or block time for a new event, meeting, study session, or work block. This is for NEW items, not modifying existing ones.
examples: plan group study {event} for calculus next friday
reserve library study room for group
reserve time for gym workout this evening
i need to plan a study {event} for {date}
hard_negatives: Creating events with full details (use calendar_event)

intents.label: search
intents.description: Find, look up, search for, filter, or query existing tasks, events, notes, assignments, or other data in the system.
examples: look up the {event} notes from last monday
look up events for spring semester
look for notes from yesterday's lecture

intents.label: status
intents.description: Request productivity analytics, completion statistics, performance metrics, or numeric tracking data. Quantifiable measures of progress.
examples: how many tasks completed this week?
how many tasks did i finish today?
what percentage of tasks are done?
how many hours logged this week?

intents.label: task_management
intents.description: Create, update, complete, delete, or track tasks, todos, assignments, or action items. Manage your task list.
examples: add studying for midterm to my tasks
create todo to finish problem set 3
create a todo for reading chapter 5

intents.label: temporal_slot_fill
intents.description: Temporal expressions like 'tomorrow', 'next week', 'this Friday' used as slot-filling responses.

intents.label: thanks
intents.description: Thank you, thanks, appreciate it. Expressing gratitude.

intents.label: time_slot_fill
intents.description: Specific times like '3pm', '10:45', 'noon' used as slot-filling responses.

intents.label: unknown
intents.description: Unclear, ambiguous, nonsensical, or out-of-scope input that doesn't match any intent.
hard_negatives: Any specific intent when user is clear

intents.label: app_info_query
intents.description: Questions about how the PulsePlan app works, pricing, features, data usage, token limits, or available integrations.
examples: how many tokens do i have left?
how do you handle my data?
hard_negatives: General help about using features (use help)

intents.label: adjust_preferences
intents.description: Change user settings or personalization preferences such as study hours, notification settings, focus mode, or UI preferences.
examples: make my default view the calendar

intents.label: user_data_query
intents.description: Ask for stored personal data, statistics, or information about user's own tasks, events, emails, or progress. Informational queries about user's data.
examples: what emails did i get this morning?
how many tasks do i have?
how am i tracking against goals?

intents.label: clarification_request
intents.description: User asks the assistant to clarify, restate, or explain something that was unclear.
examples: i don't understand what that means
